channel.title: Compiler Issue
channel.description:
Hey guys, I'm newer to the developing scene and I've stumbled across an issue while using my Virtue source that obtained on this forums. I've searched all over for a solution and I've tried a lot of different things, but my in-experience is hindering my ability to come up with a viable solution.
Here is the error that I get when running the compiler. I've specified the path to my correct location and whatnot. [img]http://i56.servimg.com/u/f56/16/16/97/89/error10.png[/img]
If you have any suggestions please let me know and thank you ahead of time! ;D

item.title: Compiler Issue
item.dc:creator: @pow_err pow err
item.description:
@pow_err wrote:

There could be many possibilities why this is happening,

  1. Right click both of the compilers in the source and client packages and change it to your current java version something like 1.6_43 1.7_45

  2. you didn’t extract the cache to the c:drive

3)something might have been played with in one of the files (Get a new source or client)

  1. watch a youtube video search up the error it gave u in the box maybe they have a video idk

If none of these helped im sorry ):
